<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5723351>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Adult females of Pulvinaria aurantii Cockerell, 1896, on a leaf of Pittosporum tobira." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5723351/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5723353>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Pulvinaria aurantii Cockerell, 1896, adult female collected from Kyushu Island in 2021. ANT, antenna; AP, anal plate; DA, dermal areolation; DMD, dorsal microduct; DS, dorsal seta; DT, dorsal tubercle; DTD, dorsal tubular duct; LG, leg; MP, multilocular pores; MS, marginal setae; POP, preopercular pores; SDP, spiracular disc pore; SSP, stigmatic spines; VMD, ventral microduct; VTD, ventral tubular ducts, types I to III. Scale bars: 100µm for ANT, AP, DA and LG; 50 μm for SSP and MS; 10 μm for all other features." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5723353/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5723355>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Partial microscopic photographs of a syntype adult female of Pulvinaria aurantii Cockerell, 1896, deposited in the Systematic Entomology Laboratory, USDA: a. anal plates and anal ring setae; b. a thin and faint but discernible sclerotic plate around a spiracle, indicated by short arrow heads; c. dorsal dermal areolation forming a reticulated pattern; d. syntype slide of P. aurantii (Photos by Scott A. Schneider)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5723355/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

